-----===== Pyella Version 0.1 - Written in Python 3 =====-----
Author: Oliver Chu (known as Jiangcheng Chu in some circles)

Pyella (pronounced "pie ey yah") is a Mint to Python translator.
Mint is a high level language that resembles JavaScript and Ruby.

Python is a very popular language that supports a large number of
built-in libraries.

Usage:

python3 Pyella.py

Will convert the file program.mint to program.py if it exists.

Doing the following...

python3 Pyella.py FILE0 FILE1 FILE2 FILE3 ... FILEN

Will convert files 0 through n to Python files, if they exist.